<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Genre (Optional):</strong> Action</p>
<p><strong>Page Layout (Optional):</strong> SCP document followed by exerpts from Parawatch forums.</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> The Foundation works hard to cover up anomalies, having extensive measures to prevent word of the Paranormal getting out. But the internet is a popular thing, especially among conspiracy theorists.</p>
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> A simple anomaly is discovered by WWS. It's a frog that when a picture is taken of it, always produces the same photo. Further more, whenever an addition copy of the photo is created, physical or digital, a non-anomalous frog of the same type is formed in the vicinity of the person who copied the picture, but WWS doesn't realize this before adopting it out. The main story of the article comes when a member of the Parawatch community gets their hands on one of the photos after being sent it by the owner and discovers it's anomalous properties. The article is set during the the Foundations management of the ongoing informational breach and how Parawatch reacts. While there will be more general responses from Parawatch as a whole, the majority of the article will focus on the original poster of the picture and their responses and circumventing of the Foundations usual cover-up procedures, such as content deletion and visual memetic amnestics. It should be noted that this Parawatch member has an attitude similar to the Foundation, attempting to understand anomalies and how they function, however the member believes that all anomalies should be known to the public, which is why they joined Parawatch. The article climaxes in an interview regarding potential Foundation recruitment of the user, which they decline due to differing ideologies the the foundation, followed be their capture, amnesation and the successful resolution of the informational breach. The article ends on a teaser that the member may have vague recollections of the Foundation.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> How the Foundation goes about a cover-up and Parawatches reaction.</p>

