														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4857554">
									

<p>Brought here on request, lets take a look.</p>
<p>Looking at the SCP itself, it seems fairly simple and straightforward. However, it may be a bit too simplistic? It falls under a thing that does a thing in my mind, a photo that when copied makes frogs appear. If that's the extent of what the SCP does, I suggest adding a bit more depth to it unless you can really pull off the comedy aspect of it. Even then, if you try that angle it may be wise to try and head down the route of a tale instead.</p>
<p>The narrative seems to have groundwork laid, but needs additional work. I'm really not sure how this frog picture almost breaks the veil as outlined. The Foundation lists Parawatch as a group that poses little threat to secrecy and the veil, and is purposefully left alone to misinform the public on the paranormal. So, I would suggest editing the threat to the veil either be more concrete or really play into the comedy aspect of the article. At the moment, I see how it could be humorous but pulling off a comedy article can be tough not to make it cliche. Either way, the idea still could use some work. You have a good start, but for me the idea is too simple and doesn't fit in with what Parawatch can do. Best of luck.</p>

							</div>

								
					
