					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/undercover-fly" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7107990); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7107990&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610157698" alt="Undercover Fly" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7107990)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/undercover-fly" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7107990); return false;" >Undercover Fly</a></span> <span class="odate time_1609367002 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Dec 2020 22:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4857749">
									

<p>Thanks for the feedback. I would just like to clarify something:</p>
<p>The SCP's effect is simplistic. I wrote it to be simplistic and be no real trouble for the foundation to contain the frog itself. The story comes when the picture ends up <strong>online</strong>. I chose Parawatch because they would be the most likely people to recognize anomalies outside the anomalous community and the most likely to spread the picture both across their platform and the internet. Parawatch has not suddenly acquired anomalous technology or contacts with another group, but they are not idiots and have been show to have proper precaution when working with <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/that-one-post-you-missed">anomalous images</a> before.</p>
<p>A group of believer in the anomalous, who have got their hands on an easily-demonstrable anomaly, who can easily convince other people of their cause by sending them a picture of the anomaly, who aren't localized, who are paranoid, who have no knowledge of the veil or why it exists and are primarily communicating and spreading using the <em>internet</em>.</p>
<p><strong>That</strong> is a concrete threat to the veil and one that the foundation would have a hard time shutting down.</p>
<p>The comedy comes from watching them try.</p>

							</div>

								
					
