<p>I've fixed and/or changed some of the minor things you had a problem with. As for having the article as an SCP article, I chose that because, as you said, Parawatch usually has no idea what's going on while the Foundation generally does. If I framed it as a Parawatch article or one from a Parawatch member's POV, <em>we</em> would get an incomplete picture of what's going on. We wouldn't know that this is on multiple threads, we wouldn't be able to identify undercover Foundation agents as such and we wouldn't know the source or aftermath of the anomaly.</p>
<p>However, as you said, the Foundation's point of view also has downsides. I'll try and think of a way to integrate both more fluidly.</p>

